race.comment: CARIBBEAN VILLA (5) was well supported and sharply better when beaten a whisker at Tatura. He's likely to give away a start again but is ready to win. ZUBBA STORM (9) brings solid well-supported placings from the provincials and races forward. He's in a top metro stable and is sure to keep improving. A player. GOD ONLY KNOWS (13) looked the goods at the jumpouts but disappointed as a short-priced favourite at Wodonga on debut. She's been kept on the fresh side and has the blinkers applied for the first time. Needs a good ride but has a handy 2kg claim and she can improve sharply for a leading stable. SPEX (14) won a Cranbourne jumpout and then wasn't too far away there on debut. Has a handy 3kg claim today and the inside barrier, and can improve into the finish.
